*Highlighted section 2: Constructor and Initialization*

The constructor initializes the student's name, ID, and GPA. It performs basic validation to ensure the GPA is within a valid range (0.0 to 4.0), and that the student ID is not empty.

```cpp
UndergraduateStudentProfile::UndergraduateStudentProfile(
    const std::string& name,
    const std::string& id,
    double academicGPA
) : fullName(name), studentID(id), gpa(academicGPA) {
    if (academicGPA < 0.0 || academicGPA > 4.0) {
        gpa = 0.0;
    }
}
```

*Highlighted section 3: Getter and Setter Implementations*

These methods allow controlled access to the private members of the class, ensuring encapsulation and data integrity.

```cpp
std::string UndergraduateStudentProfile::getName() const {
    return fullName;
}

std::string UndergraduateStudentProfile::getID() const {
    return studentID;
}

double UndergraduateStudentProfile::getGPA() const {
    return gpa;
}

void UndergraduateStudentProfile::setName(const std::string& name) {
    fullName = name;
}

void UndergraduateStudentProfile::setID(const std::string& id) {
    studentID = id;
}

void UndergraduateStudentProfile::setGPA(double gpa) {
    if (gpa >= 0.0 && gpa <= 4.0) {
        this->gpa = gpa;
    }
}
